**Problem 2: Swap Two Numbers without Using a Temporary Variable**

This problem involves swapping two numbers without using a temporary variable.

### C++ Solution
```cpp
#include <iostream>

void swap(int &a, int &b) {
    int temp = a;
    a = b;
    b = temp;
}

int main() {
    int a = 5;
    int b = 10;
    std::cout << "Before swapping: a = " << a << ", b = " << b << std::endl;
    swap(a, b);
    std::cout << "After swapping: a = " << a << ", b = " << b << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

### Java Solution
